---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base>
  <!-- Hero: animated atmospheric sky -->
  <section class="hero" aria-label="Introduction">
    <div class="sky" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg
        class="sky-svg"
        viewBox="0 0 1200 600"
        preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      >
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="sky-gradient" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#d8e8eb" />
            <stop offset="55%" stop-color="#ece8dc" />
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#f3e1c8" />
          </linearGradient>
          <filter id="cloud-blur" x="-20%" y="-20%" width="140%" height="140%">
            <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="5" />
          </filter>
          <symbol id="cloud-a" viewBox="0 0 320 100">
            <ellipse cx="80" cy="60" rx="80" ry="26" fill="#ffffff" />
            <ellipse cx="160" cy="48" rx="100" ry="32" fill="#ffffff" />
            <ellipse cx="240" cy="62" rx="74" ry="22" fill="#ffffff" />
          </symbol>
          <symbol id="cloud-b" viewBox="0 0 260 90">
            <ellipse cx="70" cy="55" rx="70" ry="22" fill="#ffffff" />
            <ellipse cx="150" cy="44" rx="80" ry="28" fill="#ffffff" />
            <ellipse cx="210" cy="58" rx="50" ry="18" fill="#ffffff" />
          </symbol>
          <symbol id="cloud-c" viewBox="0 0 200 70">
            <ellipse cx="60" cy="40" rx="56" ry="18" fill="#ffffff" />
            <ellipse cx="130" cy="34" rx="62" ry="22" fill="#ffffff" />
          </symbol>
        </defs>

        <rect width="1200" height="600" fill="url(#sky-gradient)" />

        <!-- High wisps, slow -->
        <g class="cloud-layer cloud-layer-slow" filter="url(#cloud-blur)">
          <use href="#cloud-a" x="-400" y="80" width="320" height="100" opacity="0.55" />
          <use href="#cloud-c" x="200" y="130" width="200" height="70" opacity="0.45" />
          <use href="#cloud-b" x="700" y="60" width="260" height="90" opacity="0.55" />
          <use href="#cloud-a" x="1100" y="110" width="320" height="100" opacity="0.5" />
        </g>

        <!-- Mid clouds, medium speed -->
        <g class="cloud-layer cloud-layer-medium" filter="url(#cloud-blur)">
          <use href="#cloud-b" x="-300" y="220" width="260" height="90" opacity="0.7" />
          <use href="#cloud-a" x="350" y="250" width="320" height="100" opacity="0.6" />
          <use href="#cloud-c" x="900" y="200" width="200" height="70" opacity="0.7" />
        </g>

        <!-- Low ambers near horizon, fastest -->
        <g class="cloud-layer cloud-layer-fast" filter="url(#cloud-blur)">
          <use href="#cloud-c" x="-200" y="400" width="200" height="70" opacity="0.75" style="--tint:#f3d6b3" />
          <use href="#cloud-b" x="500" y="430" width="260" height="90" opacity="0.7" />
          <use href="#cloud-a" x="950" y="410" width="320" height="100" opacity="0.7" />
        </g>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1 class="hero-name">Alfie McGlennon</h1>
      <p class="hero-affiliation">MSc Climate Change &amp; AI // University of Reading</p>
      <p class="hero-tag">Compound extremes, copula methods, and machine learning for climate risk.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About -->
  <section class="page about">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          I&rsquo;m doing the MSc in Climate Change and AI at the University of Reading.
          My dissertation builds a copula-based framework for predicting compound heat
          stress risk across European regions. The approach uses a multiplicative
          decomposition that splits climate-model bias in compound extremes into a
          marginal component and a dependence component. The ML angle is training
          XGBoost to predict Kendall&rsquo;s tau, the dependence statistic, from
          large-scale atmospheric circulation patterns. I work with ERA5 reanalysis,
          CMIP6 projections, and Destination Earth climate digital-twin data.
        </p>
        <p>
          What I keep coming back to is where climate-model biases in multivariate
          extremes actually come from, and whether ML can correct dependence
          structures directly rather than bias-correcting one variable at a time.
          Compound risk is where the gap between what climate models simulate and
          what actually hits people on the ground tends to be widest. If you treat
          hazards as independent, you systematically underestimate their joint
          probability of occurring together. Most operational climate risk work
          still does.
        </p>
        <p>
          I&rsquo;m targeting roles in climate risk analytics and reinsurance,
          particularly at Swiss Re and Munich Re, or operational meteorology
          adjacent to ECMWF. The through-line across my work is applying
          statistical and machine-learning methods to climate data where the
          outputs have operational or commercial value: quantifying compound
          risk for an insurer, improving climate-model evaluation, or optimising
          energy grid dispatch under weather uncertainty.
        </p>
        <p>
          Background: BSc Meteorology and Climate, also at Reading. Based in the
          Reading area.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- TODO: replace src below with the actual photo path once supplied (e.g. /images/alfie.jpg) -->
      <figure class="about-photo" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="photo-placeholder">
          <span>Photo</span>
        </div>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Jump-to cards -->
  <section class="page jump">
    <ul class="jump-cards">
      <li>
        <a href="/research/" class="jump-card">
          <p class="jump-card-label">Research</p>
          <p class="jump-card-line">Compound heat stress, copulas, and where climate models go wrong.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/projects/" class="jump-card">
          <p class="jump-card-label">Projects</p>
          <p class="jump-card-line">RL grid dispatch, quantum ML, climate data tooling, and more.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/AlfieMcGlennon" class="jump-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <p class="jump-card-label">GitHub</p>
          <p class="jump-card-line">Open-source work and side projects.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alfred-mcglennon-927589253/" class="jump-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <p class="jump-card-label">LinkedIn</p>
          <p class="jump-card-line">Career history and longer posts.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hero {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    height: clamp(440px, 75vh, 640px);
    overflow: hidden;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .sky {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .sky-svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .cloud-layer {
    transform-origin: center;
    will-change: transform;
  }

  .cloud-layer-slow { animation: drift-slow 180s linear infinite; }
  .cloud-layer-medium { animation: drift-medium 120s linear infinite; }
  .cloud-layer-fast { animation: drift-fast 80s linear infinite; }

  @keyframes drift-slow {
    from { transform: translateX(-8%); }
    to   { transform: translateX(8%); }
  }
  @keyframes drift-medium {
    from { transform: translateX(-12%); }
    to   { transform: translateX(12%); }
  }
  @keyframes drift-fast {
    from { transform: translateX(-18%); }
    to   { transform: translateX(18%); }
  }

  /* Alternate direction so layers move past each other */
  .cloud-layer-medium { animation-direction: alternate; }
  .cloud-layer-slow { animation-direction: alternate; }
  .cloud-layer-fast { animation-direction: alternate; }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .cloud-layer { animation: none; }
  }

  .hero-content {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .hero-name {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }

  .hero-affiliation {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: clamp(0.85rem, 1.4vw, 1rem);
    color: var(--teal-deep);
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .hero-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.7vw, 1.2rem);
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    max-width: 32ch;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  /* ── About ────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2.25rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 200px;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }
  }

  .about-photo {
    margin: 0;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 220px;
  }

  .photo-placeholder {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    background: var(--bg-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  /* ── Jump cards ───────────────────────────────────── */

  .jump {
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .jump-cards {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .jump-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .jump-card {
    display: block;
    padding: 1.5rem 0.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-left: 0;
    border-right: 0;
    background: none;
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .jump-card:hover {
    background: var(--bg-raised);
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .jump-cards li:nth-child(odd) .jump-card {
      padding-right: 1.5rem;
    }
    .jump-cards li:nth-child(even) .jump-card {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      border-left: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
  }

  .jump-card-label {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--teal-deep);
    margin: 0 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .jump-card:hover .jump-card-label {
    color: var(--amber);
  }

  .jump-card-line {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
</style>
